## Quick Start

This is a pnpm-based monorepo powered by Nx for build orchestration, caching, and task running.

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18.0.0 or higher
- pnpm 8.0.0 or higher

### Installation

```bash
# Install dependencies
pnpm install

# Setup git hooks
pnpm prepare
```

### Development

```bash
# Start all apps in development mode
pnpm dev

# Start specific app
pnpm nx dev web
```

### Building

```bash
# Build all packages and apps
pnpm build

# Build specific package
pnpm nx build ui
```

### Testing

```bash
# Run all tests
pnpm test

# Run unit tests only
pnpm test:unit

# Run integration tests
pnpm test:integration

# Run E2E tests
pnpm test:e2e

# Generate coverage reports
pnpm test:coverage
```

### Code Quality

```bash
# Lint all packages
pnpm lint

# Fix linting issues
pnpm lint:fix

# Type checking
pnpm typecheck

# Format code
pnpm format

# Check formatting
pnpm format:check
```

## Project Structure

```
{{ monorepo_name }}/
├── apps/                    # Applications (Next.js, Express, etc.)
│   └── web/                # Web application
│       └── project.json    # Nx project config (build/dev/test/lint targets)
├── packages/               # Shared packages and utilities
│   └── ui/                 # UI components
│       └── project.json    # Nx project config (build/test/lint targets)
├── nx.json                 # Nx workspace configuration (plugins, caching, target defaults)
├── pnpm-workspace.yaml     # pnpm workspace configuration
└── package.json            # Root package configuration
```

## Technologies

- **Package Manager**: pnpm
- **Build System**: Nx
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Linting**: ESLint + Prettier
- **Testing**: Vitest
- **Git Hooks**: Husky + lint-staged
- **Version Management**: Changesets

## Adding New Packages

### Adding an Application

```bash
# Generate a new Next.js app
pnpm nx g @nx/next:app apps/my-app

# Or manually:
mkdir -p apps/my-app
cd apps/my-app
pnpm init
# Add a project.json with Nx targets (see apps/web/project.json for reference)
```

### Adding a Shared Package

```bash
# Generate a new JS library
pnpm nx g @nx/js:lib packages/my-package

# Or manually:
mkdir -p packages/my-package
cd packages/my-package
pnpm init
# Add a project.json with Nx targets (see packages/ui/project.json for reference)
```

## Dependency Management

### Adding Dependencies

```bash
# Add to specific package
pnpm --filter <package-name> add <dependency>

# Add to all packages
pnpm -r add <dependency>

# Add dev dependency
pnpm --filter <package-name> add -D <dependency>
```

### Internal Dependencies

```bash
# Add internal package dependency
pnpm --filter <package-name> add <internal-package>@workspace:*
```

## Deployment

### Build for Production

```bash
# Build all packages
pnpm build

# Build specific app
pnpm nx build <app-name>
```

### Version Management

This monorepo uses Changesets for version management:

```bash
# Add changeset
pnpm changeset

# Version packages
pnpm version-packages

# Release packages
pnpm release
```

## Testing Strategy

- **Unit Tests**: Fast tests for individual functions and components
- **Integration Tests**: Tests for package interactions
- **E2E Tests**: End-to-end application tests

